    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>About Men, Women and Abortion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anagha Rangarajan letter says terminating a pregnancy should not be just a woman's decision, and fathers should have rights as well as obligations (July 5 Thomas Lynch Op-Ed article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Man's Right to Choose,'' by Thomas Lynch (Op-Ed, July 5):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Man's Right to Choose,'' by Thomas Lynch (Op-Ed, July 5):</p>
        <p>It is true that having a child and raising a child has a greater effect on a woman than on a man.</p>
        <p>I am a woman, pro-choice and  the mother of two, and I can personally attest to that. But whether to continue a pregnancy or terminate it can never be just a woman's decision.</p>
        <p>It takes two to make a baby, and  if society expects fathers to be more than sperm donors, then it should also give them more rights. They have financial obligations but few rights, and that is unfair.</p>
        <p>ANAGHA RANGARAJAN  Westwood, Mass., July 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
